  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2005-03-07",
    "date": "2005-03-22T20:28:55Z",
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exempt certain small business taxpayers from the requirements of using the accrual method of accounting and of using inventories. Allows such taxpayers to use a cash method of accounting if they meet the gross receipts test and are not engaged in farming as a corporation. Increases the amount of the gross receipts test to $10 million (currently, $5 million) and permits an annual inflation adjustment of that amount."
